  "prompt": "How do I report fake app on Appstore?",
  "response": "To report a fake app on the App Store, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the App Store**: Launch the App Store app on your iPhone or iPad.\n\n2. **Find the App**: Use the search function to locate the app that you believe is fake.\n\n3. **Scroll Down**: Once you are on the app's page, scroll down to the bottom of the page.\n\n4. **Report a Problem**: Look for the \"Report a Problem\" link. If you see this option, click on it. You may need to sign in with your Apple ID.\n\n5. **Choose the Reason**: A new page will open where you can choose the reason for your report. Select the option that is most appropriate, such as \u201cInappropriate Content\u201d or \u201cMisleading\u201d and provide details about why you believe the app is fake.\n\n6. **Submit Your Report**: After providing the necessary information, submit your report.\n\nAlternatively, you can also report an app through the Apple website:\n\n1. **Visit the Apple Support page**: Go to the [Apple Support website](https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT201359) for reporting issues.\n\n2. **Sign in**: You may need to sign in with your Apple ID.\n\n3. **Select the Appropriate Category**: Choose the option to report a problem with an app.\n\n4. **Fill Out the Form**: Provide the app's details and your reasons for reporting it as fake.\n\nApple reviews reports and may take action if they determine the app violates their guidelines. Always ensure you provide as much detail as possible to help them with their investigation.",
